{"questionId":"14620231","questionHtml":"<p>Find the binomial expansion of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;Give your answer in the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;are expressed in terms of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math>and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to expand using binomial theorem:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for seeing at least one term with a product of a binomial coefficient, power of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></math>&nbsp;and a power of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>5</mn></msup><mi>θ</mi><msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></msup><msub><mi>C</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mi>θ</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>θ</mi><msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></msup><